    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hello Friends üëã, Welcome To aGuidehub! ‚ù§Ô∏è To change the opacity of text in photopea, Select the type tool, write on the page and click the Opacity  at the top‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hello Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aGuidehub! ‚ù§Ô∏è</p>\n<p>To change the opacity of text in photopea, Select the type tool, write on the page and click the Opacity <code class=\"language-text\">drop-down arrow</code> at the top of the <code class=\"language-text\">Layers panel</code>. Click and drag the slider to adjust the <code class=\"language-text\">opacity</code>. It will change the opacity of the text.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you how I change the opacity of text in photopea.</p>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>New page.</li>\n<li>Select the type tool.</li>\n<li>Change the opacity of text.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Let‚Äôs start with the first step.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: New page.</h3>\n<p>First, go to file from the menu bar and click new or use the shortcut <strong><em>alt+ctrl+n</em></strong> and a project window will appear. Now click on create to create a new project.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4bad4cc2ce0d724e2ac0d2a104d06e05/b2c4f/new-page.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 50.632911392405056%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Photopea, new-page\"\n        title=\"Photopea, new-page\"\n        src=\"/static/4bad4cc2ce0d724e2ac0d2a104d06e05/828fb/new-page.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4bad4cc2ce0