     sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Click on page and write a text.Now you can increase the <strong><em>size of this text</em></strong> if you want to.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/e81501099c08637b08c927858dfa66d8/e5081/write-a-text.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 50.632911392405056%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Photopea, write-a-text\"\n        title=\"Photopea, write-a-text\"\n        src=\"/static/e81501099c08637b08c927858dfa66d8/828fb/write-a-text.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/e81501099c08637b08c927858dfa66d8/ff44c/write-a-text.jpg 158w,\n/static/e81501099c08637b08c927858dfa66d8/a6688/write-a-text.jpg 315w,\n/static/e81501099c08637b08c927858dfa66d8/828fb/write-a-text.jpg 630w,\n/static/e81501099c08637b08c927858dfa66d8/0ede0/write-a-text.jpg 945w,\n/static/e81501099c08637b08c927858dfa66d8/3ac88/write-a-text.jpg 1260w,\n/static/e81501099c08637b08c927858dfa66d8/e5081/write-a-text.jpg 1362w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3>Step 3: Change the opacity of text.</h3>\n<p>Select the text layer, then click the Opacity <strong><em>drop-down arrow</em></strong> at the top of the Layers panel.\nClick and drag the slider to adjust the <strong><em>opacity</em></strong>. You‚Äôll see the layer opacity change in the document window as you move the slider.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4ccdb89c7aa2ad0bc09e8fcd22345c00/38f6f/opacity.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 51.26582278481012%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Photopea, opacity\"\n        title=\"Photopea, opacity\"\n        src=\"/static/4ccdb89c7aa2ad0bc09e8fcd22345c00/828fb/opacity.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4ccdb89c7aa2ad0bc09e8fcd22345c00/ff44c/opacity.jpg 158w,\n/static/4ccdb89c7aa2ad0bc09e8fcd22345c00/a6688/opacity.jpg 315w,\n/static/4ccdb89c7aa2ad0bc09e8fcd22345c00/828fb/opacity.jpg 630w,\n/static/4ccdb89c7aa2ad0bc09e8fcd22345c00/0ede0/opacity.jpg 945w,\n/static/4ccdb89c7aa2ad0bc09e8fcd22345c00/3ac88/opacity.jpg 1260w,\n/static/4ccdb89c7aa2ad0bc09e8fcd22345c00/38f6f/opacity.jpg 1366w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Final result.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b564708558fb2054ddd2c872bdba92b8/b49b8/final.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 53.16455696202532%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Photopea, final\"\n        title=\"Photopea, final\"\n        src=\"/static/b564708558fb2054ddd2c872bdba92b8/828fb/final.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b564708558fb2054ddd2c872bdba92b8/ff44c/final.jpg 158w,\n/static/b564708558fb2054ddd2c872bdba92b8/a6688/final.jpg 315w,\n/static/b564708558fb2054ddd2c872bdba92b8/828fb/final.jpg 630w,\n/static/b564708558fb2054ddd2c872bdba92b8/0ede0/final.jpg 945w,\n/static/b564708558fb2054ddd2c872bdba92b8/3ac88/final.jpg 1260w,\n/static/b564708558fb2054ddd2c872bdba92b8/b49b8/final.jpg 1319w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>When you follow the above steps then it will change the opacity of text in photopea.</p>\n<p>All the best üëç</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How do I change the opacity of text in photopea?","tags":["Photopea"],"date":"November 01, 2022","description":"Adding to highlight words in photopea example with a step-by-step guide - aGuidehub.","social_image":"media/template/photopea.jpg"}},"prev":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to use the clone tool in photopea?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2022-11-02-how-to-use-clone-tool-in-photopea/"}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to use magic wand in photopea?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2022-11-01-how-to-use-magic-wand-in-photopea/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/2022-11-01-how-do-I-change-the-opacity-of-text-in-photopea/","prevSlug":"/blog/2022-11-02-how-to-use-clone-tool-in-photopea/","nextSlug":"/blog/2022-11-01-how-to-use-magic-wand-in-photopea/"}},
